-- pg_turbovec v1.14.0 -- Phase D breadth-parity minor release.
--
-- This file is a *reference mirror*. The authoritative install
-- script is generated by `cargo pgrx schema`.
--
-- v1.14.0 adds the multivector / hybrid-search SQL surface (driven by
-- docs/ROADMAP_BEAT_COMPETITORS.md Phase D, vs VectorChord / Qdrant):
--
--   1. turbovec.max_sim(vector[], vector[]) -> double precision
--      turbovec.max_sim_cosine(vector[], vector[]) -> double precision
--      ColBERT-style late-interaction MaxSim:
--        sum_{q in Q} max_{d in D} sim(q, d)
--      over per-token vector[] arrays. max_sim uses dot-product
--      similarity (correct for L2-normalised tokens); max_sim_cosine
--      uses cosine similarity (1 - cosine_distance). Both are
--      *similarities* (higher = better; ORDER BY ... DESC). All token
--      vectors across both arrays must share one dimension (ERROR on
--      mismatch); an empty query or empty doc scores 0.0. This is a
--      RE-RANK primitive (ANN-retrieve candidates on a pooled vector,
--      MaxSim-rerank the top-N) -- the token arrays are NOT indexed;
--      index-native late interaction remains a future phase.
--
--   2. turbovec.rrf_score(rank integer, k integer DEFAULT 60)
--          -> double precision
--      Reciprocal Rank Fusion term 1.0 / (k + rank) for fusing a
--      dense ANN ranking with a sparse / keyword ranking. Pairs with
--      the documented CTE recipe in docs/HYBRID_SEARCH.md. A
--      non-positive (k + rank) raises ERROR.
--
-- These ARE new SQL objects (functions). `cargo pgrx schema` emits
-- their CREATE FUNCTION into the authoritative 1.13.1--1.14.0 upgrade
-- script; this reference mirror does not duplicate them.
--
-- Named vectors (multiple vector columns per row) are a documented
-- SCHEMA pattern (docs/HYBRID_SEARCH.md), not new code. Out-of-core
-- BUILD (roadmap Phase D-3) already shipped in v1.12.0.
--
-- The on-disk relfile format is UNCHANGED (MetaPageData::version = 4);
-- the new SQL surface is purely additive. There is no index-AM change
-- and no on-disk migration. `ALTER EXTENSION pg_turbovec UPDATE TO
-- '1.14.0';` resolves cleanly; the additive functions are created by
-- the generated upgrade script. No REINDEX is needed -- existing
-- indexes work unchanged.
